⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Mental Seal & the Wallfacers
node 3BT · 3BT · ⟦The Mental Seal & the Wallfacers:3BT:7e420d⟧

WHO   — The Mental Seal & the Wallfacers — strategy hidden in the mind — and a machine that installs belief
WHAT  — Because sophons read everything but human thought, the Wallfacers plan in secret inside their own minds. One Wallfacer, the neuroscientist Bill Hines, builds the 'mental seal' — a device that can stamp an unshakable belief directly into a brain.
WHERE — 3BT · The Technologia of Trisolaris  Framework inputs: Remembrance of Earth's Past + adaptations; real-science verdict  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — The Wallfacer Project and the mental seal are book two; Netflix carries the Wallfacer idea through Saul Durand.
HOW   — FLUFF (the seal); thought-experiment (the Wallfacers). There is no device that installs a specific, unshakable proposition into a brain by neural manipulation — belief and brainwashing are not clean switches. The Wallfacer concept itself is a sharp thought experiment about the one thing that can't be surveilled: intention.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  They could read every word we wrote — so we hid the war behind the only wall left: the inside of a human skull.

